<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,446,761]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
Note:—This species was originally mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sledge, W. A." box="[756,914,554,580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref2904" refString="Sledge, W. A. (1982) An annotated check-list of the Pteridophyta of Ceylon. Botanical journal of the Linnean Society 84: 1 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1982. tb 00357. x" type="journal article" year="1982">Sledge (1982)</bibRefCitation>
as a putative hybrid between 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hook. &amp; Grev.) R. M. Tryon" authorityName="R. M. Tryon" baseAuthorityName="Hook. &amp; Grev." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Alsophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sinuata">
<emphasis box="[1254,1451,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Alsophila sinuata</emphasis>
(Hook. &amp; Grev.) R.M.Tryon
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thwaites) R. M. Tryon" authorityName="R. M. Tryon" baseAuthorityName="Thwaites" box="[514,979,590,617]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Alsophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hookeri">
<emphasis box="[514,716,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Alsophila hookeri</emphasis>
(Thwaites) R.M.Tryon
</taxonomicName>
considering its intermediate morphology. Later Ranil 
<emphasis box="[271,328,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
, (2010a) described it as a species after conducting a comprehensive investigation. All three species are endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[311,422,662,688]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
and confined to restricted populations in southern lowland rainforests. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ranil" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Ranil, Pushpakumara &amp; Fraser-Jenk." baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1230,1424,662,688]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Alsophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sledgei">
<emphasis box="[1230,1424,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Alsophila sledgei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an extremely rare and critically endangered species confined to small populations in Kanneliya Man and Biosphere Reserve and Sinharaja World Heritage site.
</paragraph>
